Database Server:

1. Download MySQL Server 5.0 or better from MySQL website (http://dev.mysql.com/downloads/mysql/). Make sure you are downloading
the Generally Available (Releases).
2. Install the MySQL Server.
3. Download and install MySQL Workbench (http://dev.mysql.com/downloads/tools/workbench/)
4. Download the sql file bjmpairs.sql.
5. Run MySQL Workbench and import bjmpairs.sql into the database server.
6. Download and install Connector/Net (http://dev.mysql.com/downloads/connector/net/).

BJMP-AIRS:

1. Download the latest zip file (bjmpairs.zip).
2. Unzipped the file.
3. Run the bjmpairs.exe file.

Or

1. Download the source files. You need to have Visual Studio 2008 or better to build the source files.
2. Build the source files using Visual Studi0 2008 or better.
3. Depending in your build configuration, the bjmpairs.exe is either located in the debug folder or in the release folder.

Download the following libraries to successfully build the project.

1. Office 2007 Ribbon Active Project (https://officeribbon.codeplex.com)
2. MySqlBackup.NET - MySQL Backup Solution for C#, VB.NET, ASP.NET (https://mysqlbackupnet.codeplex.com)
3. Krypton components (http://www.componentfactory.com/download).
4. imple.Data (https://github.com/markrendle/Simple.Data).
